ove & Beyond]]'' || 1982 || Metropolitan\n|-\n| ''[[Back to Birdland]]'' || 1982 || Real Time\n|-\n| ''[[Sweet Return]]'' || 1983 || [[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]] \n|-\n| ''[[The Rose Tattoo (album)|The Rose Tattoo]]'' || 1983 || Baystate (Japan)\n|-\n| ''[[Double Take (Freddie Hubbard and Woody Shaw album)|Double Take]]'' with [[Woody Shaw]]\n || 1985 || [[Blue Note Records|Blue Note]] \n|-\n| ''[[Life Flight (album)|Life Flight]]'' || 1987 || [[Blue Note Records|Blue Note]] \n|-\n| ''[[The Eternal Triangle]]'' with Woody Shaw || 1987 || [[Blue Note Records|Blue Note]] \n|-\n|''[[Stardust (Benny Golson album)|Stardust]]'' with [[Benny Golson]] || 1987 || [[Denon Records|Denon]]\n|-\n| ''[[Feel the Wind]]'' with [[Art Blakey]] || 1988 || [[Timeless Records|Timeless]]\n|-\n| ''[[Times Are Changing (album)|Times Are Changing]]'' || 1989 || Blue Note \n|-\n| ''[[Topsy \u2013 Standard Book]]'' || 1989 || Alpha/Compose\n|-\n| ''[[Bolivia (Freddie Hubbard album)|Bolivia]]'' || 1991 || [[MusicMasters Records|MusicMasters]]\n|-\n| ''[[At Jazz Jamboree Warszawa '91: A Tribute to Miles]]'' || 1991 || Starburst\n|-\n| ''[[Live at Fat Tuesday's]]'' || 1991 || MusicMasters\n|-\n| ''[[Blues for Miles]]'' || 1992 || Evidence\n|-\n| ''[[MMTC: Monk, Miles, Trane & Cannon]]'' || 1995 || MusicMasters\n|-\n| ''[[New Colors]]'' || 2000 || Hip Bop\n|-\n| ''[[On the Real Side]]'' || 2007 || Times Square\n|}\n\n===As sideman===\n''Sortable table with main artist alphabetically as primal order.''\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left; background:navajowhite; border-bottom:1px solid gray; border-top:1px solid gray;\"| Main artist\n! style=\"text-align:left; background:navajowhite; border-bottom:1px solid gray; border-top:1px solid gray;\"| Title\n! style=\"text-align:left; background:navajowhite; border-bottom:1px solid gray; border-top:1px solid gray;\"| Label\n! style=\"text-align:left; background:navajowhite; border-bottom:1px solid gray; border-top:1px solid gray;\"| Year\n|-\n| [[Manny Albam]] || ''[[The Soul of the City]]'' || [[Solid State Records|Solid State]] || 1966 \n|-\n| Roberto \u00c1vila & Sarava || ''Come to Brazil'' || [[Sonet Records|Sonet]] || 1989 \n|-\n| [[George Benson]] || ''[[The Other Side of Abbey Road]]'' || [[A&M Records|A&M]]/CTI || 1969 \n|-\n| [[Walter Benton]] || ''[[Out of This World (Walter Benton album)|Out of this World]]'' || [[Jazzland Records (American record label)|Jazzland]] || 1960 \n|-\n| [[Art Blakey]] || ''[[Mosaic (Art Blakey album)|Mosaic]]'' || [[Blue Note Records|Blue Note]] || 1961 \n|-\n| Art Blakey || ''[[Buhaina's Delight]]'' || [[Blue Note Records|Blue Note]] || 1961 \n|-\n| Art Blakey || ''[[A Jazz Hour with Art Blakey's Jazz Messengers: Blues March]]'' || Jazz Hour || 1961 [1992] \n|-\n| Art Blakey || ''[[Three Blind Mice (album)|Three Blind Mice]]'' || [[United Artists Records|United Artists]] || 1962 \n|-\n| Art Blakey || ''[[Caravan (Art Blakey album)|Caravan]]'' || [[Riverside Records|Riverside]] || 1962 \n|-\n| Art Blakey || ''[[Ugetsu (album)|Ugetsu]]'' || [[Riverside Records|Riverside]] || 1963 \n|-\n| Art Blakey || ''[[Kyoto (Art Blakey album)|Kyoto]]'' || [[Riverside Records|Riverside]] || 1964 \n|-\n| Art Blakey || ''[[Free for All (album)|Free for All]]'' || [[Blue Note Records|Blue Note]] || 1964 \n|-\n| Art Blakey || ''[[Golden Boy (Art Blakey album)|Golden Boy]]'' || [[Colpix Records|Colpix]] || 1964 \n|-\n| Art Blakey || ''[[Soul Finger (album)|Soul Finger]]'' || [[Limelight Records|Limelight]] || 1965 \n|-\n| [[Tina Brooks]] || ''[[True Blue (Tina Brooks album)|True Blue]]'' || [[Blue Note Records|Blue Note]] || 1960 \n|-\n| [[Kenny Burrell]] || ''[[God Bless the Child (Kenny Burrell album)|God Bless the Child]]'' || [[CTI Records|CTI]] || 1971 \n|-\n| [[George Cables]] || ''[[Cables' Vision]]'' || [[Contemporary Records|Contemporary]] || 1979 \n|-\n| [[Betty Carter]] || ''[[Droppin' Things]]'' || [[Verve Records|Verve]] || 1990 \n|-\n| [[Paul Chambers]] |