ke a Number from 1 to 10]]'' || [[Argo Records|Argo]] || 1961 \n|-\n| Benny Golson || ''[[Pop + Jazz = Swing]]'' \u2014 <small>jazz part also released as</small> ''Just Jazz!'' || [[Audio Fidelity Records|Audio Fidelity]] || 1962\n|-\n| Benny Golson || ''[[Time Speaks]]'' || [[Baystate Records|Baystate]] || 1982 \n|-\n| [[Dexter Gordon]] || ''[[Doin' Allright]]'' || [[Blue Note Records|Blue Note]] || 1961 \n|-\n| Dexter Gordon || ''[[Clubhouse (album)|Clubhouse]]'' || [[Blue Note Records|Blue Note]] || 1964 \n|-\n| Dexter Gordon || ''[[Generation (Dexter Gordon album)|Generation]]'' || [[Prestige Records|Prestige]] || 1972 \n|-\n| Dexter Gordon || ''[[The Other Side of Round Midnight]]'' || [[Blue Note Records|Blue Note]] || 1986 \n|-\n| [[Slide Hampton]] || ''[[Slide Hampton and His Horn of Plenty]]'' || Strand  || 1959\n|-\n| Slide Hampton  || ''[[Sister Salvation]]'' || [[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]] || 1960 \n|-\n| Slide Hampton || ''[[Drum Suite (Slide Hampton album)|Drum Suite]]'' || Epic || 1962\n|-\n| [[Herbie Hancock]] || ''[[Takin' Off]]'' || [[Blue Note Records|Blue Note]] || 1962 \n|-\n| Herbie Hancock || ''[[Empyrean Isles]]'' || [[Blue Note Records|Blue Note]] || 1964 \n|-\n| Herbie Hancock || ''[[Maiden Voyage (Herbie Hancock album)|Maiden Voyage]]'' || [[Blue Note Records|Blue Note]] || 1965 \n|-\n| Herbie Hancock || ''[[Blow-Up (soundtrack)|Blow-Up]]'' || [[MGM Records|MGM]] || 1966 \n|-\n| Herbie Hancock || ''[[VSOP (album)|V.S.O.P.]]'' || [[Columbia Records|Columbia]] || 1977 \n|-\n| Herbie Hancock || ''[[The Quintet (V.S.O.P. album)|V.S.O.P. The Quintet]]'' || [[Columbia Records|Columbia]] || 1977 \n|-\n| Herbie Hancock || ''[[Tempest in the Colosseum|V.S.O.P. Tempest in the Colosseum]]'' || [[Columbia Records|Columbia]] || 1977 \n|-\n| Herbie Hancock || ''[[V.S.O.P. Live Under the Sky]]'' || [[Columbia Records|Columbia]] || 1979 \n|-\n| Herbie Hancock || [[Round Midnight (soundtrack)|''Round Midnight'' (soundtrack)]] || [[Columbia Records|Columbia]] || 1986 \n|-\n| [[Jimmy Heath]] || ''[[The Quota]]'' || [[Riverside Records|Riverside]] || 1961 \n|-\n| Jimmy Heath || ''[[Triple Threat (Jimmy Heath album)|Triple Threat]]'' || [[Riverside Records|Riverside]] || 1962 \n|-\n| [[Joe Henderson]] || ''[[Big Band (Joe Henderson album)|Big Band]]'' || [[Verve Records|Verve]] || 1996 \n|-\n| [[Andrew Hill (jazz musician)|Andrew Hill]] || ''[[Pax (album)|Pax]]'' || [[Blue Note Records|Blue Note]] || 1965 [1975] \n|-\n| Andrew Hill || ''[[Compulsion (album)|Compulsion!!!!!]]'' || [[Blue Note Records|Blue Note]] || 1965 \n|-\n| [[Bobby Hutcherson]] || ''[[Dialogue (Bobby Hutcherson album)|Dialogue]]'' || [[Blue Note Records|Blue Note]] || 1965 \n|-\n| Bobby Hutcherson || ''[[Components (album)|Components]]'' || [[Blue Note Records|Blue Note]] || 1965 \n|-\n| Bobby Hutcherson || ''[[Knucklebean]]'' || [[Blue Note Records|Blue Note]] || 1977 \n|-\n| Bobby Hutcherson || ''[[Highway One]]'' || [[Columbia Records|Columbia]] || 1978 \n|-\n| [[Milt Jackson]] || ''[[Sunflower (Milt Jackson album)|Sunflower]]'' || [[CTI Records|CTI]] || 1973 \n|-\n| [[Milt Jackson]] || ''[[Goodbye (Milt Jackson album)|Goodbye]]''\u2014 <small>trumpet on \"S.K.J.\" only</small> || [[CTI Records|CTI]] || 1974 \n|-\n| [[Billy Joel]] || ''[[52nd Street (album)|52nd Street]]'' \u2014 <small>trumpet on \"Zanzibar\" only</small> || [[Columbia Records|Columbia]] || 1978 \n|-\n| [[Elton John]] || ''[[Reg Strikes Back]]'' || [[Rocket Record Company|Rocket]]/[[Mercury Records|Mercury]] || 1988 \n|-\n| [[J. J. Johnson]] || ''[[J.J. Inc.]]'' || [[Columbia Records|Columbia]] || 1961 \n|-\n| [[Quincy Jones]] || ''[[I Dig Dancers]]'' || Mercury || 1960\n|-\n| Quincy Jones || ''[[The Quintessence]]'' || Impulse! ||1962\n|-\n| Quincy Jones || ''[[Golden Boy (Quincy Jones album)|Golden Boy]]'' || Mercury || 1964\n|-\n| Quincy Jones || ''[[I/We Had a Ball]]'' || [[Limelight Records|Limelight]] || 1965\n|-\n| Quincy Jones || ''[[Walking in Space]]'' || [[A&M Records|